[cron:8b380d56-7314-4ba9-b4c4-ea11d3e5ca6f PR Review Patrol (High Frequency)] High-frequency PR patrol for bills-bot.

Repo: /home/bill/.openclaw/workspace-build/bills-bot/

Do this each run:
1) List open PRs in BillChirico/bills-bot.
2) Skip bot-authored PRs by default (e.g., coderabbitai, dependabot[bot], renovate[bot]) unless Bill explicitly instructs otherwise.
3) For remaining PRs, count unresolved review threads.
4) If no unresolved threads on eligible PRs: respond exactly `NO_REPLY`.
5) If unresolved threads exist:
   - Spawn ONE sub-agent PER PR (parallel), never batch PRs together.
   - Use agentId `build`, model `anthropic/claude-opus-4-6`, thinking `high`.
   - Include full unresolved thread details (thread id, file path, line, issue summary).
   - Instruct spawned agents to read and follow CODING.md, fix all review comments (including nitpicks unless nonsensical/breaking/redundant), run tests/coverage, resolve threads.
   - Instruct spawned agents NOT to post PR summary comments unless Bill explicitly asks.
   - Have spawned agents report completion summary back to parent agent.
   - After spawning, send Bill a concise Discord DM status update:
     - channel: discord
     - target: user:191633014441115648
     - accountId: pip-build
     - include PR numbers and unresolved thread counts.
6) If any spawned run fails/stalls, note it in DM and respawn once.

Keep updates concise and action-oriented.
Current time: Wednesday, February 11th, 2026 ‚Äî 11:07 PM (America/New_York)

# GitHub Skill

Use the `gh` CLI to interact with GitHub. Always specify `--repo owner/repo` when not in a git directory, or use URLs directly.

## Pull Requests

Check CI status on a PR:

```bash
gh pr checks 55 --repo owner/repo
```

List recent workflow runs:

```bash
gh run list --repo owner/repo --limit 10
```

View a run and see which steps failed:

```bash
gh run view <run-id> --repo owner/repo
```

View logs for failed steps only:

```bash
gh run view <run-id> --repo owner/repo --log-failed
```

## API for Advanced Queries

The `gh api` command is useful for accessing data not available through other subcommands.

Get PR with specific fields:

```bash
gh api repos/owner/repo/pulls/55 --jq '.title, .state, .user.login'
```

## JSON Output

Most commands support `--json` for structured output. You can use `--jq` to filter:

```bash
gh issue list --repo owner/repo --json number,title --jq '.[] | "\(.number): \(.title)"'
```

arguments.command:
set -euo pipefail
cd /home/bill/.openclaw/workspace-build/bills-bot
prs_json=$(gh pr list --repo BillChirico/bills-bot --state open --json number,title,author,headRefName,url)
# Build report JSON with unresolved thread details for eligible PRs
report='[]'
for pr in $(echo "$prs_json" | jq -r '.[].number'); do
  pr_meta=$(echo "$prs_json" | jq -c ".[] | select(.number==$pr)")
  author=$(echo "$pr_meta" | jq -r '.author.login // ""')
  # Skip bot-authored PRs by default
  if [[ "$author" =~ \[bot\]$ ]] || [[ "$author" == "coderabbitai" ]] || [[ "$author" == "renovate" ]] || [[ "$author" == "dependabot" ]]; then
    report=$(echo "$report" | jq --argjson meta "$pr_meta" '. + [{pr:$meta, skipped:true, reason:"bot-authored", unresolved:[]}]')
    continue
  fi

  threads=$(gh api graphql \
    -f owner='BillChirico' \
    -f name='bills-bot' \
    -F number=$pr \
    -f query='query($owner:String!,$name:String!,$number:Int!){repository(owner:$owner,name:$name){pullRequest(number:$number){reviewThreads(first:100){nodes{id isResolved path line originalLine startLine originalStartLine comments(first:20){nodes{body author{login} createdAt}}}}}}}' \
    --jq '.data.repository.pullRequest.reviewThreads.nodes')

  unresolved=$(echo "$threads" | jq '[.[] | select(.isResolved==false) | {
    id,
    path,
    line: (.line // .originalLine // .startLine // .originalStartLine),
    summary: ((.comments.nodes[0].body // "") | gsub("\\r|\\n"; " ") | .[0:220])
  }]')

  report=$(echo "$report" | jq --argjson meta "$pr_meta" --argjson unr "$unresolved" '. + [{pr:$meta, skipped:false, unresolved:$unr}]')
done

echo "$report" | jq '.'

arguments.command:
set -euo pipefail
cd /home/bill/.openclaw/workspace-build/bills-bot
python3 - <<'PY'
import json, subprocess, re, sys

def run(cmd):
    p = subprocess.run(cmd, capture_output=True, text=True)
    if p.returncode != 0:
        print(p.stderr, file=sys.stderr)
        raise SystemExit(p.returncode)
    return p.stdout

prs = json.loads(run(["gh","pr","list","--repo","BillChirico/bills-bot","--state","open","--json","number,title,author,headRefName,url"]))
report = []
for pr in prs:
    author = (pr.get("author") or {}).get("login") or ""
    is_bot = author.endswith("[bot]") or author in {"coderabbitai","renovate","dependabot"}
    if is_bot:
        report.append({"pr":pr,"skipped":True,"reason":"bot-authored","unresolved":[]})
        continue

    query = "query($owner:String!,$name:String!,$number:Int!){repository(owner:$owner,name:$name){pullRequest(number:$number){reviewThreads(first:100){nodes{id isResolved path line originalLine startLine originalStartLine comments(first:20){nodes{body author{login} createdAt}}}}}}}"
    out = run(["gh","api","graphql","-f","owner=BillChirico","-f","name=bills-bot", "-F", f"number={pr['number']}", "-f", f"query={query}"])
    data = json.loads(out)
    threads = (((data.get("data") or {}).get("repository") or {}).get("pullRequest") or {}).get("reviewThreads", {}).get("nodes", [])
    unresolved = []
    for t in threads:
        if t.get("isResolved"):
            continue
        comments = ((t.get("comments") or {}).get("nodes") or [])
        summary = comments[0].get("body","") if comments else ""
        summary = re.sub(r"[\r\n]+", " ", summary)[:220]
        line = t.get("line") or t.get("originalLine") or t.get("startLine") or t.get("originalStartLine")
        unresolved.append({
            "id": t.get("id"),
            "path": t.get("path"),
            "line": line,
            "summary": summary,
        })
    report.append({"pr":pr,"skipped":False,"unresolved":unresolved})

print(json.dumps(report, indent=2))
PY
